# claudux cursor rules (short)

Why: docs are generated. Manual edits get wiped, cause drift, and waste review time.

Do:
- Change generators/templates in `lib/**` and re-run claudux.
  Examples: `lib/vitepress/config.template.ts`, `lib/docs-generation.sh`, `lib/ui.sh`, `lib/templates/**`.
- Use CI-only override for GitHub Pages: `docs/.vitepress/config.pages.ts` with `vitepress build -c .vitepress/config.pages.ts`.

Don’t:
- Edit `docs/**` or `docs/.vitepress/**` directly.
- Use env vars or `sed` to mutate the base path.

Defaults:
- Local/dev base: `/` in `docs/.vitepress/config.ts`.
- This repo’s Pages base: `/claudux/` only via the CI override file above.
- Branding: lowercase "claudux"; prefer single-line comments in source.
- Cleanup: only remove stale docs, never source code.


